ing practices. At the same time, McElroy accounts for the ways Romanians are resisting Silicon Valley capitalist logics, where anticapitalist and anti-imperialist activists and protesters build on socialist-era worldviews not to restore state socialism but rather to establish more just social formations. Attending to the violence of Silicon Valley imperialism, McElroy reveals technocapitalism as an ultimately unsustainable model of rapacious economic and geographic growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGentrificationxSocial aspectszCaliforniazSan Francisco. 0aGentrificationxSocial aspectszRomania. 0aHuman geographyzRomania. 0aRacismzRomania. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspectszCaliforniazSan Francisco. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspectszRomania. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059219?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059219423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059219/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles